@baseUrl = http://localhost:5242
@email = test@example.com
@otp = 222340

### ──────────────── STEP 1: Authenticate ────────────────

### 1a. Send OTP (check console for [DEV OTP] output)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/email/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "{{email}}" }

### 1b. Verify OTP — captures accessToken into @token variable
# @name verify
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/email/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "{{email}}", "otp": "{{otp}}" }

###
@token = {{verify.response.body.accessToken}}

### 1c. View captured token
# The @token variable is set above. Run 1b first, then run this.
# The response body will show subjects — confirming auth works.
# To see the raw token, look at the verify response body in 1b.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/subjects
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ──────────────── STEP 2: Get Subject IDs ────────────────

### 2a. List subjects
# @name subjects
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/subjects
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

@subject1Id = {{subjects.response.body.data[0].id}}
@subject2Id = {{subjects.response.body.data[1].id}}

### ──────────────── STEP 3: Mock Engine Endpoints ────────────────

### 3a. Generate Mock (Endpoint 1)
# Generates a mock with 5 random questions from 2 subjects
# @name generate
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/generate
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subjectIds": ["{{subject1Id}}", "{{subject2Id}}"],
  "questionCount": 5,
  "timeLimitMinutes": 30
}

###
@mockId = {{generate.response.body.mockSessionId}}
@q1Id = {{generate.response.body.questions[0].questionId}}
@q2Id = {{generate.response.body.questions[1].questionId}}
@q3Id = {{generate.response.body.questions[2].questionId}}

### 3b. Get Mock Session (Endpoint 2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/{{mockId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3c. Submit Answers (Endpoint 3)
# Answer 3 questions — options chosen arbitrarily for testing
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/{{mockId}}/answers
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "answers": [
    { "questionId": "{{q1Id}}", "displayOrder": 1, "selectedOption": "A", "timeTakenMs": 30000 },
    { "questionId": "{{q2Id}}", "displayOrder": 2, "selectedOption": "B", "timeTakenMs": 45000 },
    { "questionId": "{{q3Id}}", "displayOrder": 3, "selectedOption": "C", "timeTakenMs": 25000 }
  ]
}

### 3d. Complete Mock (Endpoint 4)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/{{mockId}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3e. Get Results (Endpoint 5)
# Only accessible after completion
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/{{mockId}}/results
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3f. Get History (Endpoint 6)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/history?page=1&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3g. Retake Incorrect (Endpoint 7)
# Creates a new mock with only questions answered incorrectly
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/generate/retake-incorrect
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "previousMockSessionId": "{{mockId}}"
}

### ──────────────── STEP 4: Edge Case Tests ────────────────

### 4a. 401 without token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{ "subjectIds": ["00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"], "questionCount": 5 }

### 4b. 400 validation — no subjects
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/generate
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "subjectIds": [], "questionCount": 5 }

### 4c. 400 validation — zero question count
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/generate
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "subjectIds": ["{{subject1Id}}"], "questionCount": 0 }

### 4d. 400 — complete an already completed mock
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/{{mockId}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4e. 404 — non-existent mock session
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/mocks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4f. Get a question ID for SR review
# Uses the first subject's slug from your DB. Replace if needed.
# @name questions
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/questions?subjectSlug=anaesthesia&page=1&pageSize=1

###
@questionId = {{questions.response.body.data[0].id}}

### ──────────────── STEP 5: Spaced Repetition (Phase 2.4) ────────────────

### 5a. Get Due Questions (Endpoint 1)
# Initially empty if no reviews have been done
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/spaced-repetition/due?page=1&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5b. Review Question — Correct Answer (Endpoint 2)
# Creates QuestionSchedule, returns SM-2 result
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/spaced-repetition/{{questionId}}/review
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "selectedOption": "A", "timeTakenMs": 15000 }

### 5c. Review Same Question Again — Interval Increases
# Second correct review: newInterval=6 per SM-2
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/spaced-repetition/{{questionId}}/review
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "selectedOption": "A", "timeTakenMs": 10000 }

### 5d. Review — Incorrect Answer (EaseFactor decreases to 1.3)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/spaced-repetition/{{questionId}}/review
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "selectedOption": "B", "timeTakenMs": 8000 }

### 5e. Get Spaced Repetition Stats (Endpoint 3)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/spaced-repetition/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5f. Due Questions — After Reviews
# Should now show scheduled cards
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/spaced-repetition/due?page=1&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5g. 401 without token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/spaced-repetition/{{questionId}}/review
Content-Type: application/json

{ "selectedOption": "A", "timeTakenMs": 10000 }

### 5h. 400 — non-existent question
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/spaced-repetition/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/review
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "selectedOption": "A", "timeTakenMs": 10000 }

### ──────────────── STEP 6: Analysis Engine (Phase 2.5) ────────────────

### 6a. Analyze Batch (Endpoint 1)
# Uses question IDs captured from earlier steps
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analysis/batch
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "questionIds": ["{{q1Id}}", "{{q2Id}}", "{{q3Id}}"]
}

### 6b. Analyze Batch — Empty validation (400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analysis/batch
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "questionIds": []
}

### 6c. Analyze Batch — Invalid question ID (400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analysis/batch
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "questionIds": ["00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"]
}

### 6d. Get Dashboard (Endpoint 2)
# Returns overall stats, streak, XP, strongest/weakest subjects
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analysis/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6e. Get Question History (Endpoint 3)
# Uses questionId from SR review step
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analysis/question/{{questionId}}/history
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6f. Get Question History — No attempts (returns empty array, not 404)
# Uses a valid question that the user has never attempted
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analysis/question/{{q2Id}}/history
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6g. 401 without token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analysis/dashboard

### 6h. 401 — Batch without token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/analysis/batch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "questionIds": ["00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"]
}

### 6i. 401 — Question History without token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analysis/question/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/history
